inner
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

products 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "ans:zero-inner-products"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{w}=c_{1}\mathbf{b}_{1}+c_{2}\mathbf{b}_{2}+\cdots+c_{n}\mathbf{b}_{n}$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{1}\rangle=\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{2}\rangle=\cdots=\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{n}\rangle=0$
\end_inset

 means 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{1}\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{1}\rangle=c_{2}\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{2}\rangle=\cdots=c_{n}\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{b}_{n}\rangle=0$
\end_inset

.
 By properties 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "enu:inner-product-symmetry"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "enu:inner-product-preserve-sum"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "enu:inner-product-preserve-scalar-mult"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 of inner product spaces (see page 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand pageref
reference "enu:inner-product-preserve-sum"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle\mathbf{w},c_{1}\mathbf{b}_{1}\rangle=\langle\mathbf{w},c_{2}\mathbf{b}_{2}\rangle=\cdots=\langle\mathbf{w},c_{n}\mathbf{b}_{n}\rangle=0$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle\mathbf{w},c_{1}\mathbf{b}_{1}+c_{2}\mathbf{b}_{2}+\cdots+c_{n}\mathbf{b}_{n}\rangle=0$
\end_inset

.
 But 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{1}\mathbf{b}_{1}+c_{2}\mathbf{b}_{2}+\cdots+c_{n}\mathbf{b}_{n}=\mathbf{w}$
\end_inset

 so 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle\mathbf{w},\mathbf{w}\rangle=0$
\end_inset

 and by property 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "enu:inner-product-zero"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{w}=\mathbf{0}$
\end_inset

.
 
